hopobject.body: Incorrect PIN marina pharmacy group dubai As Secretary of State John Kerry said last week, the country is war weary. Our history of retrenchment and isolationism is reasserting itself. Americans have always been reluctant to enter foreign conflicts. Indeed many of our forebears came here to escape such quagmires. While the public tends to rally ‘round the troops once they are committed, if the rationale is poorly explained and things take a turn for the worst, that support can wane quickly. That risk gives the president's decision to engage the public and their representatives some merit.
